{"type":"message","id":"78229945","parentId":"1f9ccb52","timestamp":"2026-04-27T23:04:39.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gmail has 2 new emails, iCloud has several but the \"!\" flag means it's unread and \"R\" means read. Let me check the iCloud emails more carefully - the ! flag on ID 8 means it's flagged/unread. Let me read those emails to get details.\n\nActually, I should read the Gmail emails to get summaries too. Let me read them all.\n\nFor iCloud, ID 9 has no flags (so unread but not flagged), ID 8 has \"!\" which means flagged and \"R\" means read. Wait, actually looking at himalaya flags: space means unread, \"!\" means flagged, \"R\" means read. So:\n\n\n- 9: unread, not flagged (and recent, 19:06)\n- 8: flagged, read (12:20)\n- 7: read (older)\n- 6: read (older)\n\nI need to fetch the content of these emails to provide summaries. Let me pull the details from both Gmail and iCloud, then send them along with the cron results.\n","thinkingSignature":"3e7c816823cf0e9530c0c5f643e9bbc762eec891b95714a58c748c027d295ef2"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me read those emails to get summaries.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_43hgrtkf41mz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gog gmail read 19dd1079ac331d29 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | head -30","timeout":20}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_43hgrtkf41mz_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gog gmail read 19dd0fb5c12b98dd --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1 | head -30","timeout":20}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_43hgrtkf41mz_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"himalaya message read 9 --account icloud 2>&1","timeout":20}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_43hgrtkf41mz_4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"himalaya message read 8 --account icloud 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":477,"output":434,"cacheRead":19584,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTo